    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Bush and Gore Get 2 1/2-Minute PBS Forums</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>PBS is offering major presidential candidates two-and-a-half minutes to address public on topics of their choosing after The Newshour With Jim Lehrer, beginning on October 25 and running through November 3 (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>PBS is offering the major presidential candidates two and a half minutes to address the public on topics of their choosing after ''The Newshour With Jim Lehrer.</p>
        <p>Starting on Wednesday and running through Friday, Nov. 3, one candidate will speak each night, and their statements will be shown on alternating nights.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>PBS is offering the major presidential candidates two and a half minutes to address the public on topics of their choosing after ''The Newshour With Jim Lehrer.</p>
        <p>Starting on Wednesday and running through Friday, Nov. 3, one candidate will speak each night, and their statements will be shown on alternating nights.</p>
        <p>The Bush campaign won a coin toss to determine the order in which the candidates present their messages. As a result Mr. Gore will begin the series on Wednesday, and Mr. Bush will finish it on Nov. 3.</p>
        <p>THE 2000 CAMPAIGN</p>
      </block>
